1 kept in the ordinary course of the transient lodging tax collector’s business.
2 (2) The tax imposed under this section becomes due when the occupancy of the transient lodging
3 with respect to which the tax is imposed ends.
4 (3)(a) The tax shall be collected by the transient lodging provider or transient lodging interme-
5 diary that collects the consideration charged for occupancy of the transient lodging, or a transient
6 lodging intermediary described in ORS 320.300 (12)(c), as applicable.
7 (b) The transient lodging tax collector may withhold a collection reimbursement charge of five
8 percent of the amount collected under this subsection.
9 (4) The tax imposed under this section is in addition to and not in lieu of any local transient
10 lodging tax.
