6 SECTION 3. ORS 320.303 is amended to read:
7 320.303. (1) A transient lodging tax collector shall, upon payment, provide to the person that
8 pays the consideration charged for occupancy of transient lodging an invoice, receipt or other sim-
9 ilar document that clearly sets forth the sum of all transient lodging taxes charged for the occu-
10 pancy of the transient lodging.
11 (2) The invoice, receipt or other similar document shall describe the portion of the tax
12 imposed at the rates set forth in ORS 320.305 (1)(a)(B) and (C) as a “nature conservation
13 fee.”
14 [(2)] (3) The invoice, receipt or other similar document may be in any form that the transient
15 lodging tax collector uses in the ordinary course of business.
16 SECTION 4. ORS 496.303 is amended to read:
17 496.303. (1) The Fish and Wildlife Account is established in the State Treasury, separate and
18 distinct from the General Fund. All moneys in the account are continuously appropriated to the
19 State Fish and Wildlife Commission. The Fish and Wildlife Account shall consist of the moneys in
20 its various subaccounts and any moneys transferred to the account by the Legislative Assembly.
21 Unless otherwise specified by law, interest earnings on moneys in the account shall be paid into the
22 State Treasury and credited to the State Wildlife Fund.
23 (2)(a) The Fish Screening Subaccount is established in the Fish and Wildlife Account. The sub-
24 account shall consist of:
25 (A) All penalties recovered under ORS 536.900 to 536.920.
26 (B) All moneys received pursuant to ORS 498.306.
27 (C) All gifts, grants and other moneys from whatever source that may be used to carry out the
28 provisions of ORS 498.306.
29 (D) All moneys received from the sale of angling licenses dedicated by ORS 497.124.
30 (b) All moneys in the subaccount shall be used to carry out the provisions of ORS 315.138,
31 498.306 and 509.620. However, moneys received from the sale of angling licenses dedicated by ORS
32 497.124 shall be expended only to carry out the provisions of law relating to the screening of water
33 diversions.
34 (3) The Fish Endowment Subaccount is established in the Fish and Wildlife Account. The sub-
35 account shall consist of transfers of moneys authorized by the Legislative Assembly from the State
36 Wildlife Fund and gifts and grants of moneys from whatever source for the purpose of paying the
37 expense of maintaining fish hatcheries operated by the [department] State Department of Fish and
38 Wildlife.
39 (4) The Migratory Waterfowl Subaccount is established in the Fish and Wildlife Account. All
40 moneys received by the commission from the sale of art works and prints related to the migratory
41 waterfowl stamps shall be deposited in the subaccount. Moneys in the subaccount may be expended
42 only for activities that promote the propagation, conservation and recreational uses of migratory
43 waterfowl and for activities related to the design, production, issuance and arrangements for sale
44 of the migratory waterfowl stamps and related art works and prints. Expenditures of moneys in the
45 subaccount may be made within this state, in other states or in foreign countries, in such amounts
