7 to the subaccount. Moneys in the subaccount may be expended only for halibut population studies
8 and other research.
9 (6) The Upland Bird Subaccount is established in the Fish and Wildlife Account. All moneys
10 received by the commission [State Fish and Wildlife Commission] from the sale of upland bird
11 stamps, from the sale of any art works and prints related to the upland bird stamps and from private
12 hunting preserve permit fees shall be deposited in the subaccount. Moneys in the subaccount may
13 be expended only for promoting the propagation and conservation of upland birds and the acquisi-
14 tion, development, management, enhancement, sale or exchange of upland bird habitat, and for ac-
15 tivities related to the design, production, issuance and arrangements for sale of the upland bird
