21 Moneys in the subaccount may be used for the purposes specified in ORS 496.242.
22 (8) The Marine Shellfish Subaccount is established in the Fish and Wildlife Account. Interest
23 earnings on moneys in the subaccount shall be credited to the subaccount. All moneys received by
24 the commission from the sale of resident and nonresident shellfish licenses pursuant to ORS 497.121
25 shall be deposited in the subaccount. Moneys in the subaccount shall be used for the protection and
26 enhancement of shellfish for recreational purposes, including shellfish sanitation costs and the cost
27 of enforcement of wildlife laws pertaining to the taking of shellfish. The State Fish and Wildlife
28 Director, or a designee, the Director of Agriculture, or a designee, and the Superintendent of State
29 Police, or a designee, shall jointly make a recommendation to the Governor for inclusion in the
30 Governor’s budget beginning July 1 of each odd-numbered year.
31 (9)(a) The Mountain Sheep Subaccount is established in the Fish and Wildlife Account, consist-
32 ing of moneys collected under ORS 497.112 (2)(a) to (c).
33 (b) All moneys in the subaccount shall be used for the propagation and conservation of mountain
34 sheep, for research, development, management, enhancement and sale or exchange of mountain
35 sheep habitat and for programs within the state that in the discretion of the commission most di-
36 rectly benefit mountain sheep resources of this state.
37 (10)(a) The Antelope Subaccount is established in the Fish and Wildlife Account, consisting of
38 moneys collected under ORS 497.112 (2)(a) to (c).
