17 prints and art works under ORS 496.571.
18 (B) All moneys received by the Department of Revenue under ORS 320.335 (3)(b).
19 (C) Moneys appropriated to the State Department of Fish and Wildlife for deposit in the
20 subaccount or otherwise transferred to the subaccount.
21 (D) Any gifts, grants, contributions or other donations for use as described in paragraph
22 (c) of this subsection that are received by the State Department of Fish and Wildlife or the
23 commission from any public or private source and caused to be deposited in the subaccount
24 or otherwise transferred to the subaccount.
25 (c) Moneys in the subaccount shall be used:
26 (A) To promote, implement, revise or enhance the policies in the State Wildlife Action
27 Plan, or any subsequent iterations of that policy, as determined by the department; and
28 (B) To satisfy nonfederal fund matching requirements for a conservation or restoration
29 program designed to recover and manage the species in greatest need of conservation and
30 the habitats essential to conservation of those species, as determined by the department.
31 (d) Moneys in the subaccount may be used for activities related to the design, production,
32 issuance and arrangement for sale of the habitat conservation stamps, prints and art works
