1 SECTION 5. ORS 496.571 is amended to read:
2 496.571. (1) The State Fish and Wildlife Commission may issue an annual habitat conservation
3 stamp. The fee for the stamp may not exceed $50.
4 (2) The commission shall arrange, by contest or other appropriate means, for the selection of the
5 design of the annual habitat conservation stamp authorized by subsection (1) of this section and for
6 the production and sale of the stamps.
7 (3) The commission may produce the number of stamps the commission considers appropriate
8 and may make stamps available for the creation of art prints and other related art works and may
9 arrange for the sale of stamps, prints and art works to persons desiring to purchase those items.
10 (4) In carrying out its duties, functions and powers with regard to the habitat conservation
11 stamp, the commission may contract for the performance of those duties, functions and powers. The
12 contract may include, among other matters, provisions for advance payment or reimbursement for
13 services performed pursuant to the contract. All costs and expenses incurred pursuant to this sec-
14 tion shall be paid from the [Oregon Conservation Strategy] Recovering Oregon’s Wildlife Fund
15 Subaccount established under ORS 496.303.
16 SECTION 6. The amendments to ORS 320.303, 320.305 and 320.335 by sections 1 to 3 of this
17 2026 Act apply to consideration charged on or after January 1, 2027, for the sale, service or
18 furnishing of transient lodging.
19 SECTION 7. This 2026 Act takes effect on the 91st day after the date on which the 2026
20 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly adjourns sine die.
